# Bottom Sheet Token Rules

Bottom sheet components MUST use ONLY these tokens:
- tokens.bottomSheetBg
- tokens.bottomSheetText
- tokens.bottomSheetSecondaryText
- tokens.bottomSheetSeparator

NEVER use in bottom sheets:
- tokens.sceneBackground
- tokens.surface
- tokens.accentPrimary
- tokens.accentMuted
- tokens.textOnAccent
- tokens.borderSubtle

These themed tokens are for the main app UI only.

## Bottom Sheet Components

All components in the bottom sheet system:
- BaseBottomSheet.tsx - Core template component
- BottomSheetDivider.tsx - Separator line primitive
- BottomSheetSectionTitle.tsx - Section header primitive
- BottomSheetRow.tsx - Pressable row primitive
- SupportSheet.tsx - Support page (migrated)
- SettingsSheet.tsx - Settings page (to be migrated)
- ExerciseSelectionSheet.tsx - Exercise selection (to be migrated)
- ExerciseDetailSheet.tsx - Exercise details (to be migrated)

## Why This Separation Matters

Bottom sheets use system colors (PlatformColor) that adapt to light/dark mode automatically and are completely independent of the app's theme palettes (grounded/calm/uplifting). This ensures:

1. Consistent minimal aesthetic across all bottom sheets
2. Proper light/dark mode support
3. No color mixing between main app UI and bottom sheets
4. Native iOS-style appearance
